\pard\sb480\sa120\b\fs36 TMJ Treatment\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa160 \par
\pard\sa200 The temporomandibular joint (TMJ) is the hinge that connects your jaw to your skull, and when it is not working properly, the effects can ripple outward \emdash  jaw pain, headaches, clicking or locking, neck and shoulder tension, and difficulty opening your mouth fully. TMJ disorders have multiple potential causes including bite imbalance, teeth grinding, stress, and joint wear. Treatment focuses on identifying the root cause and reducing the strain on the joint.\par
\pard\sa200 TMJ issues are often underdiagnosed because the symptoms do not always point obviously to the jaw. Recurring headaches or persistent neck tension are sometimes traced back to a bite problem that nobody thought to look for. Getting a proper assessment from a dentist with experience in this area can be the thing that finally connects the dots. Treatment is usually conservative \emdash  most patients improve significantly without surgery.\par
\pard\sa100 \par
\pard\sb200\sa100\b\fs26 When Should You Consider It?\b0\fs22\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa80 \bullet\tab {\b Jaw pain or soreness, especially in the morning:} Morning pain often indicates clenching or grinding during sleep, which puts significant strain on the joint.\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa80 \bullet\tab {\b Clicking, popping, or grating sounds when you open or close your mouth:} These sounds suggest the joint disc is not moving as it should and warrant assessment.\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa80 \bullet\tab {\b Headaches that seem to concentrate around the temples:} Tension in the jaw muscles frequently radiates into headaches \emdash  this is more common than most people realise.\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa80 \bullet\tab {\b Difficulty opening your mouth fully or jaw locking:} Restricted range of motion is a sign that the joint or surrounding muscles are under significant strain.\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa80 \bullet\tab {\b Neck and shoulder tightness that does not resolve with stretching:} Jaw tension and body tension are closely connected \emdash  addressing one often helps the other.\par
\pard\sa100 \par
\pard\sb200\sa100\b\fs26 What to Expect\b0\fs22\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa100 1.\tab {\b Assessment and bite analysis.} Dr. Sezer evaluates the joint, your bite, and your symptoms to understand the likely cause and the severity of the issue.\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa100 2.\tab {\b Custom treatment plan.} Depending on findings, treatment may include a night guard, bite adjustment, physiotherapy referral, or a combination of approaches.\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa100 3.\tab {\b Monitoring and follow-up.} TMJ treatment is typically a process \emdash  progress is tracked and the approach is adjusted as your symptoms improve.\par
\page
\pard\sb480\sa120\b\fs36 Night Guards\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa160 \par
\pard\sa200 A night guard is a custom-fitted oral appliance that sits between your upper and lower teeth while you sleep. It cushions the impact of grinding (bruxism) or clenching, protecting your tooth enamel, reducing strain on the jaw joint, and absorbing forces that would otherwise be transmitted directly to your teeth and surrounding bone. Unlike over-the-counter guards, a custom night guard is made from a precise impression of your teeth and fits comfortably enough that most people forget they are wearing it.\par
\pard\sa200 Many people grind their teeth without realising it \emdash  they only find out when a dentist spots unusual wear, or when a partner mentions the sound at night. Left unaddressed, bruxism can cause significant damage: enamel erosion, cracked teeth, jaw pain, and worsening TMJ symptoms. A night guard will not stop you from grinding, but it prevents the damage that grinding causes \emdash  and for many people, it makes a noticeable difference to how they feel in the morning.\par
\pard\sa100 \par
\pard\sb200\sa100\b\fs26 When Should You Consider It?\b0\fs22\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa80 \bullet\tab {\b You wake up with jaw soreness or facial tension:} This is one of the most reliable signs of nighttime grinding or clenching.\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa80 \bullet\tab {\b Your dentist has noticed unusual tooth wear:} Flattened or thinning enamel is a clear indicator that protective treatment is overdue.\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa80 \bullet\tab {\b You have had a cracked or chipped tooth without an obvious cause:} Grinding is a common culprit and often the first time patients put two and two together.\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa80 \bullet\tab {\b You are experiencing TMJ symptoms:} A night guard is frequently the first line of treatment for TMJ-related jaw pain and clicking.\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa80 \bullet\tab {\b High stress levels:} Stress and grinding are closely linked \emdash  a guard protects you during periods when you are more likely to clench.\par
\pard\sa100 \par
\pard\sb200\sa100\b\fs26 What to Expect\b0\fs22\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa100 1.\tab {\b Impressions and fitting.} Moulds of your teeth are taken and sent to a dental lab, where your guard is custom-fabricated to your exact bite.\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa100 2.\tab {\b Delivery and adjustment.} The guard is fitted and checked for comfort and bite balance \emdash  minor adjustments ensure it sits perfectly.\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa100 3.\tab {\b Ongoing care guidance.} You will be shown how to clean and store your guard, and Dr. Sezer will check it at regular appointments to make sure it is still doing its job.\par
