\pard\sb480\sa120\b\fs36 Pediatric Dentistry\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa160 \par
\pard\sa200 Children's dental care at Dolphin Dental is built around one goal: making sure your child associates the dentist with something calm and positive. The team takes time with young patients, explains everything in age-appropriate language, and never rushes. Early visits focus on gentle examination, preventive care, and helping children feel genuinely comfortable in the chair \emdash  because how they feel about the dentist as a child shapes how they think about their oral health for the rest of their lives.\par
\pard\sa200 Starting dental visits early matters. The Canadian Dental Association recommends a child's first visit within six months of their first tooth coming in, or by their first birthday. Beyond cavity prevention, early visits allow the dentist to monitor how the teeth and jaw are developing, identify any early concerns, and coach parents on diet and home care habits. It is far easier to prevent a problem than to fix one \emdash  and the habits formed in childhood tend to stick.\par
\pard\sa100 \par
\pard\sb200\sa100\b\fs26 When Should You Consider It?\b0\fs22\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa80 \bullet\tab {\b Your child's first tooth has appeared:} This is the signal to book a first visit \emdash  it is never too early to start on the right foot.\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa80 \bullet\tab {\b Your child has not seen a dentist yet and is school-age:} It is not too late \emdash  a gentle, unhurried first visit can undo any anxiety and establish a positive routine.\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa80 \bullet\tab {\b You have noticed a cavity or visible discolouration on a baby tooth:} Baby teeth matter and cavities in them can affect the development of adult teeth beneath.\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa80 \bullet\tab {\b Your child grinds their teeth or breathes through their mouth at night:} These are worth discussing with the dentist as they can affect jaw and tooth development.\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa80 \bullet\tab {\b You want to establish a relationship before anything is ever wrong:} Familiarity with the dentist makes every future visit easier \emdash  for your child and for you.\par
\pard\sa100 \par
\pard\sb200\sa100\b\fs26 What to Expect\b0\fs22\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa100 1.\tab {\b A warm, unhurried welcome.} The first visit is about comfort \emdash  the team introduces your child to the environment, the tools, and the faces before any examination begins.\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa100 2.\tab {\b Gentle examination and cleaning.} Depending on your child's age and comfort, a simple examination and light cleaning are performed, with findings explained to you in plain language.\par
\pard\fi-360\li360\sa100 3.\tab {\b Guidance for home care and next steps.} You will leave with practical advice on brushing, diet, and when to come back \emdash  everything you need to keep your child's smile on track.\par
